Software Development Documentation for QuantAi

1. Introduction
QuantAi is a scalable and secure software platform designed to streamline user management, questionnaire programming, data collection, processing, collaboration, and AI-driven automation. It serves researchers, businesses, and organizations by providing an all-in-one solution for surveys, data analysis, and community engagement.

This document details the module-wise breakdown, features, functionalities, development timelines, and payment structures to ensure a structured and efficient development process.

2. Project Overview

Objective
Develop a scalable and secure platform with the following core functionalities:
•	User management with role-based access
•	Advanced questionnaire programming
•	Multi-channel data collection
•	Data processing and visualization
•	Collaboration tools for researchers
•	CRM and marketing automation integrations
•	AI-driven automation and predictive analytics
•	Custom branding and white-Labeling

Module-wise Development Plan
Core Modules & Functionalities

User Management with Role-Based Access
Objective: Provide secure and customizable user access control to ensure data integrity and role-specific functionalities.

Features & Functionalities:
•	Multi-tier User Roles:
o	Admin (Full system control)
o	Researcher (Create & manage surveys, analyze data)
o	Moderator (Manage community & responses)
o	Respondent (Participate in surveys)
•	Authentication & Security:
o	Email/Social login (Google, LinkedIn)
o	Two-factor authentication (2FA)
o	Single Sign-On (SSO) for enterprise users
•	User Profiles & Custom Attributes:
o	Custom fields for user segmentation
o	Activity logs for audit trails
•	Invite & Onboarding System:
o	Bulk user upload via CSV
o	Automated welcome emails

1. Respondent Onboarding
•	Multi-channel signup (Email, Social Login, Phone, SSO)
•	Profile verification (Email, OTP, KYC for high-value surveys)
•	Demographic profiling (Age, Gender, Location, Income, Education, Occupation)
•	Interest-based segmentation (Product preferences, Industry expertise)
•	Gamified onboarding (Progress bars, Badges, Welcome bonuses)

2. Researcher/Enterprise Onboarding
•	Role-based access (Admin, Researcher, Analyst, Collaborator)
•	Company verification (Domain-based email, Business registration)
•	Billing & Subscription plans (Free, Pro, Enterprise)

Advanced Questionnaire Programming
Objective: Enable dynamic, logic-driven survey creation with a user-friendly interface.

Features & Functionalities:
•	Drag-and-Drop Survey Builder:
o	Pre-built templates (Likert scales, MCQs, open-ended)
o	Conditional logic (skip logic, branching)
•	Multi-Format Support:
o	Text, audio, video, and image-based questions
o	Multi-language surveys (auto-translation via AI)
•	Advanced Logic & Customization:
o	Randomization of questions/options
o	Variable piping (carry responses to later questions)
o	API-triggered surveys (external event-based)

1. Survey Builder (DIY Interface)
•	Drag-and-drop editor
•	Pre-built templates (CSAT, NPS, Product Feedback, Market Segmentation)
•	Multi-language support (Auto-translation, RTL language support)
•	White-Labeling & branding customization

2. Question Types
•	Single/Multiple Choice
•	Dropdown & Slider Scales
