Question Types

Standard Question Types

1.	Single Selection (Radio Buttons)
o	Only one option can be selected.
o	Example: "What is your gender? (Male / Female / Other)"

2.	Multiple Selection (Checkboxes)
o	Multiple options can be selected.
o	Example: "Which social media platforms do you use? (Facebook, Instagram, Twitter, LinkedIn)"

3.	Dropdown Menu
o	Compact list for single selection.
o	Useful for long lists (e.g., country selection).

4.	Text Input (Open-Ended)
o	Short Answer: Single-line text (e.g., "Name").
o	Long Answer: Paragraph response (e.g., "Describe your experience").

5.	Rating Scales
o	Likert Scale (e.g., 1-5, "Strongly Disagree" to "Strongly Agree").
o	Star Rating (e.g., 1-5 stars for product reviews).
o	NPS (Net Promoter Score) (0-10: "How likely are you to recommend us?").
o	Slider Scale (Visual drag slider for granular responses).

6.	Ranking (Drag & Drop or Numerical)
o	Prioritize items (e.g., "Rank these features from most to least important").

7.	Matrix/Grid Questions
o	Multiple questions in a table format (e.g., "Rate the following aspects: Price, Quality, Service").
8.	Date/Time Picker
o	Select date, time, or both (e.g., "When is your preferred appointment time?").

9.	File Upload
o	Allow respondents to upload documents, images, or videos.

10.	Signature Capture
•	For e-signatures (e.g., consent forms).

11.	Contact Information
•	Structured fields for name, email, phone, etc.

B. Advanced & Interactive Question Types

12.	Image Choice
o	Select from images instead of text (e.g., "Which logo do you prefer?").

13.	Audio/Video Response
o	Record voice or video answers (useful for qualitative research).

14.	Geolocation
o	Capture GPS coordinates (e.g., "Share your location for store visits").

15.	CAPTCHA / Human Verification
o	Prevent bot responses.

16.	Calculated Fields
o	Auto-compute values (e.g., "Total score = Q1 + Q2").

17.	Hidden Fields
o	Pass metadata (e.g., user ID, referral source) without respondent input.

18.	Interactive Sliders & Heatmaps
o	Visual feedback on images (e.g., "Click areas you like on this webpage").

19.	Conjoint Analysis (Advanced Market Research)
o	Trade-off questions to measure preferences (e.g., pricing vs. features).

20.	MaxDiff (Maximum Difference Scaling)
o	Forces respondents to choose most/least preferred options.

2. Branching & Logic Features

A. Skip Logic (Conditional Question Display)
•	Show/Hide Questions based on previous answers.
o	Example: If "Do you own a car?" = No, skip car-related questions.

B. Branching (Survey Flow Control)
•	Jump to a Section based on responses.
o	Example: If "Age < 18", redirect to parental consent section.

C. Piping (Dynamic Text Insertion)
•	Reuse previous answers in later questions.
o	Example: "You mentioned your favourite brand is [Q1 Answer]. Why?"



D. Looping & Randomization
1.	Question Looping
o	Repeat a block of questions for multiple items (e.g., "Rate each of these 5 products").
2.	Randomization
o	Shuffle question/answer order to reduce bias.

E. Advanced Logic Types
1.	Calculated Logic
o	Use formulas to determine branching (e.g., "If Score > 80, show premium offer").
2.	Quota Management
o	Close survey after a set number of responses (e.g., "Stop after 100 females answer").
3.	Timed Questions
o	Force a minimum/maximum time per question.

3. Advanced Features from Leading Platforms

A. Qualtrics-Specific Features
•	Conjoint & MaxDiff Analysis (for pricing research).
•	Sentiment Analysis & Text iQ (AI-driven open-text insights).
•	Panel Management (recruit and track respondents over time).

B. SurveyMonkey-Specific Features
•	Benchmarking (compare results against industry standards).
•	A/B Testing (test different survey versions).

C. QuestionPro-Specific Features
•	Longitudinal Studies (track changes over time).
•	Mobile Offline Surveys (sync when back online).

D. Type form-Specific Features
•	Conversational Forms (chat-like survey experience).
•	Logic Jumps (smooth transitions between questions).

2. Core Features

2.1 Survey Programming
•	Question Types: Support for multiple question types (e.g., multiple choice, open-ended, rating scales).
•	Customization: Ability to customize survey appearance with logos, images, and branding.
•	Logic & Branching: Advanced logic features such as skip logic, branching, and conditional questions.
•	Validation: Data validation and quality control through survey logic and conditions.
•	Preview & Testing: Ability to preview and test surveys before launch.
•	Import/Export: Import and export survey questions and data.

2.2 Data Collection
•	Participant Management: Invite and manage participants, including email invitations and reminders.
•	Real-Time Tracking: Track response rates, completion rates, and data quality in real-time.
•	Data Export: Export raw data and metadata for further analysis.

2.3 Data Analysis
•	Data Cleaning: Tools for cleaning, processing, and analysing data with statistical software.
•	Custom Reports: Create and run custom reports and analysis.
•	Weighting & Segmentation: Apply weighting and segmentation to data.
•	Automation: Automate data cleaning and quality control procedures.

2.4 Data Visualization
•	Charts & Graphs: Create and customize charts, graphs, and visualizations.
•	Interactive Dashboards: Build interactive dashboards for data display.
•	Export Options: Export visualizations in various formats (PNG, SVG, PDF).

2.5 Final Findings
•	Report Generation: Create and customize reports and presentations.
•	Export Formats: Export reports in various formats (PPT, PDF).
•	Collaboration: Share and collaborate on reports and presentations.
•	Automation: Automate report generation and distribution.
3. Advanced Features

3.1 Campaign Management
