•	Authentication: Use secure authentication methods, including two-factor authentication (2FA).
•	Compliance: Ensure compliance with data protection regulations (e.g., GDPR, CCPA).

7.2 Regular Audits
•	Security Audits: Conduct regular security audits to ensure data protection.
•	Anonymous Surveys: Offer anonymous survey options for sensitive data.

8. Technical Architecture

8.1 Frontend
•	Responsive Design: Use frameworks like React.js or Angular for responsive web design.
•	Mobile App: Develop a companion mobile app using Flutter or React Native.

8.2 Backend
•	Scalable Backend: Use scalable backend technologies like Node.js, Django, or Ruby on Rails.
•	Database Management: Implement database management with PostgreSQL or MongoDB.
•	Cloud Hosting: Utilize cloud hosting services (AWS, Google Cloud, Azure).

8.3 APIs
•	RESTful/GraphQL APIs: Provide APIs for integrations with third-party tools.
•	Webhooks: Implement webhooks for real-time updates.

8.4 Analytics
•	Integration: Integrate with analytics tools like Google Analytics or Mixpanel.
•	Custom Analytics: Develop custom analytics for survey performance tracking.

9. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

9.1 User Metrics
•	Total Subscribers: Track the overall number of subscribers.
•	Conversion Rate: Monitor the percentage of website visitors who become subscribers.
•	Onboarding Completion Rate: Measure the percentage of users who complete the onboarding process.
•	User Engagement: Track how often subscribers interact with the platform.
•	Retention Rate: Monitor the percentage of subscribers who continue to use the platform over time.

9.2 Survey Metrics
•	Survey Completion Rate: Track the percentage of subscribers who complete surveys.
•	Time to Onboard: Measure the average time it takes for a user to complete the onboarding process.

9.3 Marketing Metrics
•	Cost per Acquisition (CPA): Calculate the average cost required to acquire a new subscriber.
•	Churn Rate: Monitor the percentage of subscribers who stop using the platform.
•	Geographic Distribution: Understand where subscribers are located.
•	Device Metrics: Analyse the devices and browsers used by subscribers.

Unique AI/ML Features for QuantAi
QuantAi can offer the following unique AI/ML capabilities:

1.	AI-Powered Survey Design:
o	Automatically suggest survey questions and applicable response options based on research objectives. (Target audiences, target market etc)
o	Use NLP to refine questions for clarity and relevance.

2.	Dynamic Data Collection:
o	Adjust survey questions in real-time based on respondent answers (adaptive questioning).
o	Use AI to identify and re-engage drop-off respondents.

3.	Insights Visualization:
o	Automatically generate interactive dashboards with key insights highlighted.
o	Use AI to recommend the most relevant visualizations for the data.

4.	Voice and Video Analytics:
o	Analyse voice and video responses using AI to extract insights (e.g., tone, emotion, context).
o	Provide a richer understanding of customer feedback.

5.	AI-Driven Panel Management:
o	Use ML to match respondents with surveys based on their profiles and past behaviour.
o	Predict and prevent panel fatigue by optimizing survey frequency.

