Dashboards/ Statistics
-	Widget for showing Total, Active, & Closed Campaigns
-	Conversion reports: These reports track the number of conversions that have been generated by affiliates, as well as the value of those conversions.
-	Click-through rate (CTR) reports: These reports track the number of clicks that have been generated by affiliates, as well as the percentage of clicks that lead to conversions.
-	Cost per acquisition (CPA) reports: These reports track the amount of money that has been spent on affiliate marketing, as well as the average amount of money that has been spent to acquire a customer.
-	Revenue reports: These reports track the total amount of revenue that has been generated by affiliate marketing.
-	Performance reports: These reports track the overall performance of affiliate marketing campaigns, and can be used to identify areas where improvement is needed.
-	Geographic reports: These reports track the geographic location of affiliates and their visitors, which can be helpful for targeting marketing campaigns.
-	Device reports: These reports track the devices that affiliates and their visitors are using, which can be helpful for optimizing marketing campaigns for different devices.
-	Referral source reports: These reports track the sources of traffic that is being driven to the affiliate's website, which can be helpful for identifying the most effective marketing channels.

