IMPORTANT KPI

1.	Total Subscribers:
•	Track the overall number of subscribers to measure the growth of your user base.
2.	Conversion Rate:
•	Monitor the percentage of website visitors who become subscribers. This helps assess the effectiveness of your onboarding process.
3.	Onboarding Completion Rate:
•	Measure the percentage of users who successfully complete the onboarding process. This can highlight potential issues in the user journey.
4.	User Engagement:
•	Track how often subscribers interact with your platform, such as logging in, participating in research, or completing surveys.
5.	Retention Rate:
•	Monitor the percentage of subscribers who continue to use the platform over time. A high retention rate indicates a healthy user base.
6.	Survey Completion Rate:
•	If your platform involves surveys or research tasks, track the percentage of subscribers who complete these activities.
7.	Time to Onboard:
•	Measure the average time it takes for a user to complete the onboarding process. A shorter time to onboard is generally preferable.
8.	User Feedback and Satisfaction:
•	Gather feedback from subscribers through surveys or other means to assess their satisfaction with the onboarding process and overall experience.
9.	Social Sharing and Referrals:
•	Monitor the number of subscribers who refer others to join the platform. This can indicate user satisfaction and the viral nature of your service.
10.	Platform Traffic:
•	Track the overall traffic to your platform to understand the effectiveness of your marketing efforts in attracting potential subscribers.
11.	Cost per Acquisition (CPA):
•	Calculate the average cost required to acquire a new subscriber. This helps evaluate the efficiency of your marketing and onboarding strategies.
12.	Churn Rate:
•	If applicable, monitor the percentage of subscribers who stop using the platform. A high churn rate may indicate issues with user experience or content relevance.
13.	Geographic Distribution of Subscribers:
•	Understand where your subscribers are located to tailor your content and marketing strategies to specific regions.
14.	Device and Browser Metrics:
•	Analyze the devices and browsers used by subscribers to ensure your platform is optimized for the most common preferences.
15.	Conversion Funnel Metrics:
•	Break down the onboarding process into stages and monitor conversion rates at each stage to identify potential bottlenecks.

Outline for Quant AI Platform

1. Core Features

1.	User Management
o	User registration and authentication (email, social media, or SSO).
o	Role-based access control (Admin, Researcher, Participant).
o	Profile management for users (researchers and participants).
2.	Questionnaire Programming: 45 – 60 Question Type
o	Drag-and-drop interface for creating surveys.
o	Advanced logic features:
	Skip logic, branching, and piping.
	Conditional questions based on responses.
	Randomization of questions or answer options.
o	Integration with external APIs for real-time data fetching.
o	Pre-built templates for common survey types (e.g., NPS, customer satisfaction, market research).
o	Multi-language support for global surveys.
3.	Data Collection
o	Multiple survey distribution channels:
	Email invitations.
	Social media integration (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.).
	WhatsApp and SMS integration.
	Embeddable survey links for websites.
o	Offline data collection (with sync when online).
o	Mobile-friendly and responsive survey design.
o	Gamification features to increase participation (e.g., rewards, badges).
4.	Data Processing
o	Real-time data tabulation and reporting.
o	Advanced data visualization tools:
	Charts, graphs, and heatmaps.
	Customizable dashboards.
o	Data filtering and segmentation.
o	Export options (Excel, CSV, PDF, SPSS).
o	AI-powered sentiment analysis for open-ended responses.
5.	Community Building
o	Participant registration and profile creation.
o	Interest-based tagging for participants (e.g., demographics, preferences).
o	Internal survey participation for registered users.
o	External survey participation with filtered invites based on interests.
o	Reward system for participation (e.g., points, gift cards).
o	Tracking and analytics for each distribution channel.
o	Customizable survey links for different channels.

6.	Omni-Channel Survey Distribution
o	Unified platform for distributing surveys across multiple channels.
o	Tracking and analytics for each distribution channel.
o	Customizable survey links for different channels.




2. Advanced Features

1.	Collaboration Tools
o	Team collaboration for researchers (shared access to surveys and data).
o	Commenting and annotation features for survey design and analysis.
o	Version control for surveys.
2.	Integration Capabilities
o	CRM integration (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot).
o	Marketing automation tools (e.g., Mailchimp, Marketo).
o	Payment gateway integration for paid surveys.
o	API for custom integrations with third-party tools.
3.	Security and Compliance
o	GDPR, CCPA, and other data privacy compliance.
o	Data encryption (in transit and at rest).
o	Two-factor authentication (2FA) for secure login.
o	Anonymous survey options for sensitive data.
4.	AI and Automation
o	AI-driven survey recommendations based on research goals.
o	Automated data cleaning and outlier detection.
o	Predictive analytics for survey outcomes.
5.	Custom Branding
o	White-label surveys with custom branding (logos, colors, fonts).
o	Custom domain support for survey links.
o	Personalized email templates for invitations.

3. User Experience (UX) and Interface Design

1.	Intuitive Dashboard
o	Centralized dashboard for managing surveys, data, and participants.
o	Quick access to frequently used features.
o	Real-time notifications for survey responses and updates.
2.	Mobile App
o	Companion mobile app for researchers and participants.
o	Offline survey capabilities for participants.
o	Push notifications for survey reminders.
3.	Accessibility
o	WCAG compliance for accessibility.
o	Screen reader support.
o	High-contrast themes for visually impaired users.

. Technical Architecture

1.	Frontend
o	Responsive web design using frameworks like React.js or Angular.
o	Mobile app development using Flutter or React Native.
2.	Backend
o	Scalable backend using Node.js, Django, or Ruby on Rails.
o	Database management (PostgreSQL, MongoDB).
o	Cloud hosting (AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure).
3.	APIs
o	RESTful or GraphQL APIs for integrations.
o	Webhooks for real-time updates.
4.	Analytics
o	Integration with tools like Google Analytics or Mixpanel.
o	Custom analytics for survey performance.